image of Thomasius more clearly and to dispel stereotypic received thinking about him, thus opening up new avenues for exploration and interpretation. The volume assembles the papers delivered at an interdisciplinary colloquium in Magdeburg in June 1995.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aKongress. 4aMagdeburg ‹1995›. 4aThomasius, Christian. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aBorgstedt, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraungart, Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuchholz, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanneberg, Lutz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDreitzel, Horst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrunert, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHartung, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHäfner, Ralph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJaumann, Herbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKimmich, Dorothee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKühlmann, Wilhelm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuig, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarti, Hanspeter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaurer, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPetrus, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScattola, Merio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneiders, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 a